<p>I missed out by learning a&nbsp;programming language first&nbsp;rather than trying to understand the computer on the hardware level. As programmers we are controlling the hardware and eventually even if you&#39;re programming in Javascript you need to know about memory and how the language works. So understanding&nbsp;binary data,&nbsp;persistent and temporary memory, CPU, SPU, GPU,&nbsp;networking and more&nbsp;is crucial even if you&#39;re a web developer this still applies to you.</p>

